    <h1 class="toggler tl_info">FOR WEB DEVELOPERS AND WEB ADMINISTRATORS<span class="tl_green plus">+</span><span class="tl_green minus">-</span></h1>
    <div class="toggle_section" style="display:block; padding:5px 25px;">
        <h1>HTML 5:</h1>
        <p>ReadSpeaker only works in an HTML5 environment.</p>
        <p>ReadSpeaker uses the ID of an element to define what to read. The URL of the current page will be sent to ReadSpeaker, together with the language and the ID of the container</p>
        <p>ReadSpeaker will then replace the content of the given container with a readable markup and will stream the voice via mp3.</p>
        <hr>
        <h1>Javascript:</h1>
        
        <br><p>So bare in mind that, because of the markup replacement, hooked javascript events of elements will get lost. </p>
        
        <p>
            There is an event fired to the document, when ReadSpeaker has changed the content of a container.
            <br>You can interact with it by doing something like this:
            <br>
            <code>
                <span style="color:#AFAFAF;">&lt;script&gt;</span>
                <br>document.addEventListener(<span style="color:#EE0000;">"onRsContentChanged"</span>, function(<span style="color:#EE0000;">e</span>) {
                <br>
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="color:#00AA00;">id</span> = <span style="color:#EE0000;">e.detail.container</span>; //id of the updated container
                <br>
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;/*
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Here you can rehook your javascript
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * to the elements within the changed container.
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * e.g. jQuery:
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * $("#"+<span style="color:#00AA00;">id</span>).slideDown(500);
                <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; */
                <br>
                <br>});
                <br><span style="color:#AFAFAF;">&lt;/script&gt;</span>
            </code>
        </p>
        <div style="padding-left:25px; border-left: 1px solid #bebebe;">
